==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Clarification
<hw>Clar`i*fi*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>clarification</ets>, L. <ets>clarificatio</ets>
glorification.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or process of making
clear or transparent, by freeing visible impurities; <as>as, the
<ex>clarification</ex> of wine</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of freeing from obscurities.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>clarification</qex> of men's ideas.</q>
<rj><qau>Whewell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clarifier</ent>⟦br⟧
